        <td bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>I am going to put this on a petition site for people to sign if its a complete list.  </P><P>If you want an easier to read version check at:<BR><a href="http://darqsmoke.8m.net/Necromancers.htm" target="_blank">http://darqsmoke.8m.net/Necromancers.htm</a></P><P></P><P>	At level 46, a Necromancer’s role changes.  In the past, they could play solo and group efficiently.  Post 46 though, the focus changes from outdoor to indoor or planar zones.  This can be made evident in the obvious popularity of zones like Temple of Veeshan, Kanor’s Castle, Chardok, Velks Labyrinth, Sebilis, the Hole, and the Planes.  High level equipment, at least the good stuff, are located on monsters in dungeons, so that is where players go.  Necromancers need to be changed in order to be able to adapt to the new playing style.  </P><P><BR>Check these locations for more descriptive reasons behind the proposed changes:<BR>Necro Site 1<BR>Necro Site 2	<BR>Necro Site 3<BR>Necro Site 4</P><P>Proposed Changes :</P><P>Pets (w/ focus):</P><P>Level 49 pet (unchanged) -- Invoke Death<BR>Hit Points: 2350<BR>Max Hit: 57<BR>Additional Abilities: Bash/Kick 25, Life Drain (40)</P><P>Level 53 pet -- Minion of Shadows<BR>Hit Points: 2900<BR>Max Hit: 59<BR>Additional Abilities: Backstab 165, Life Drain (50)</P><P>Level 56 pet -- Servant of Bones<BR>Hit Points: 3400<BR>Max Hit: 61<BR>Additional Abilities: Flying Kick 73, Life Drain (60)</P><P>Level 59 pet -- Emissary of Thule (spectre)<BR>Hit Points: 3950<BR>Max Hit: 61<BR>Additional Abilities: Bash/Stun: 40, Life Drain (80), Spectre Stun (25), Fear Immunity<BR>Additional Costs: Peridot (1); no bone chips (its a spectre!)</P><P>Also please fix the graphic and the lifetap of our pets</P><P>Pet Commands:</P><P>/pet hold – this is designed to counter act poor pathing and pet bugs.  This should be in from level 1, and not an alternate advancement skill.</P><P>/pet heel – basically the same effect as above.  Allows the casters to set a distance in which the pet can’t go out of.  This is designed to make moving in a dungeon with a pet safer.  Just in case pet strays into an area of bad pathing, this will prevent him from getting more that a certain distance from the caster.  This could be an alternate advancement skill, but I think it should be in from level one also.</P><P>Spell Changes:</P><P>First off, move all spells to locations reachable, with one group, by a caster of that level.  Also make them common drop.  Also make sure that when resistance was changed some time ago, that it effected not only direct damage spells but also damage over time spells.  </P><P>Lvl 54 Succussion of Shadows:<BR>Mana: 375<BR>Effect: Decrease mob AC by 75 and gives 75AC to EACH person in group<BR>Duration: 5mins</P><P>Lvl 56 Crippling Claudication:<BR>Mana: 375<BR>Effect: Decrease mob ATK by 100 and give 100ATK to EACH person in group.<BR>Duration: 5mins</P><P>Lvl 58 Mind Wrack:<BR>Mana: 300<BR>Effect: Gives everyone in group a 12 mana per tick regen for 2 mins <BR>Duration: 2 mins<BR>Recast Time: instant<BR>Note:  Stacks with everything except clarity line.  </P><P>(This is basically a mana buff.  Its 1 mana better than clarity 2 but it costs 5135 more mana.  I personally like to see 15 mana per tick, Clarity 2 would still be much more efficient )</P><P>Lvl 60 Zevfeer's Theft of Vitae:<BR>Mana: 600<BR>Effect: Drains mob's HP by 1800, and gives 300hp to EACH person in group, over 2 minutes.  .<BR>Duration:  2mins <BR>(We are the Masters of Lifetapping) </P><P>Note on all of these:  Make the recast times on all of these spells instant, but place an effect, with duration in line with the spells duration, on its target so the spell can not be chain cast.  Also make this effect not cancel out mez, like DoTs do.  </P><P>Quivering Veil of Xarn – Remove the illusion, and the night time only effect.  </P><P>Trucidation– Remove the need for an essence emerald.  Replace it with another regent or none at all.  </P><P>Infussion – Remove the need for an essence emerald.  Change to a mana DoT.  Decrease the mana gained by half.  Make it require a peridot.</P><P>Levant – Remove the nighttime only stipulation.</P><P>Arch Lich – Add ultravision and fear immunity.</P><P>Personal Summon Corpse – make sure this spell is dropping. </P><P><BR>Proposed new spell ideas:</P><P>Screaming Banshee (L49)  - Damage shield (25)<BR>Banshee possession(L44)  - Targeted version of Banshee Aura (12)<BR>Screaming Banshee Possession (54)  - Target version of Screaming Banshee (25)<BR>Reaper’s Aura(L40) – Grim Aura Upgrade – Increases Attack of Target by 25.<BR>Shadow Storm(L49) - Takes 75 AC from target and gives to self<BR>Paralyzing Fear (L54) – AoE effect Stun/Mem blur spell, with a lower resist.  Duration 20 seconds  <BR>Dead Man Walking (44) – Dead man floating, without the floating.  No zone restriction<BR>Group Dead Man Walking(49) – Group version of Dead Man Walking.<BR>Decay (55) - Disease based Deflux similar to the disease based Touch of Night at level 60. <BR>Death Peace (51) – Same as the Shadow Knight Version.  We are the parent class.  <BR>Engulfing Shadows (59) – Two ideas for this spell.  Either a group version of Levant or a spell that changed it to night in the zone. <BR>Painful death (53) – Works only on lvl 49 Pet.  Increases pet hitpoints to 2900. Adds a 12 point damage shield (ie banshee aura).  Increases pet lifetap power by 10 percent.  Indoor only (and raid only zones)<BR>Reapers Curse (56) – Works only on the lvl 49 Pet.  Increases pet hitpoints to 3400.  Adds a 25 point Damage shield.  (ie Screaming Banshee suggested spell).  Increases pet lifetap power by 20 percent.  Increases pets immunity to fear.  Indoor and raid only zones.<BR>Gift of Thule (60) – Works only on the lvl 59 pet.  Increases pet hitpoints to 4000.  Adds a 32 point Damage Shield.  Increases pet spells efficiency by 20 percent.  Increase Max hit to 61.   Indoor and raid only zones.</P><P>Spell Line: Resist Fear (16-54) – Increase target’s resistance to fear<BR>Spell Line: Degenerate (16-54) – Decreases amount target regains hitpoints.<BR>Spell Line:  Confusion (16-54) – Decreases the amount in which the target regains mana. (would be a good mage line too)</P><P>Epic</P><P>There are many ideas on this.  To save man power at Verant, I would suggest a contest.  Necromancers submit pictures to Verant with effect.  Design team picks 10 best ideas.  The player base votes on these ideas, with the option of not choosing any.  The winner gets the newest version of the epic, and the necro epic is changed to his design.  </P><P>Thanks</P><P></P><P>Smaaug Darqsmoke<BR>Iksar Necromancer<BR>Brell Serilis</font></td>
